<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-137-576  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 137 576.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Feb 12 1990 v12 n7 p67(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Finalsoft interactive program attempts translation to Spanish;unfortunately, a lot gets lost in the translation. (SoftwareReview) (Finalsoft Corp.'s Translate) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kaliczak, Anne.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Translate is a $495 software package from Finalsoft Corp thattranslates business documents between English and Spanish.andP;  Theprogram works adequately if simple sentences with straightforwardgrammar are used, but it needs to have several inconsistenciesworked out for it to be reliable.andP;  Finalsoft does not claim thatthe program is foolproof.andP;  Indeed all documents must be proofed byan experienced Spanish speaker before they are used.andP;  The programtranslates on a line-by-line basis, but does not contain wordprocessing or printing features.andP;  In order to view the wholedocument, it must be transferred to a word processor.andP;  Theprogram's recurring problems involve substituting adjectives fornouns, translating verbs as nouns and transposing terms in aphrase.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Finalsoft Corp. (products).andO;Product:   TranSlate (Computer program).andO;Topic:     EvaluationForeign LanguagesLanguage TranslationSoftware PackagesSpanish Language.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>